                        <name type="name" key="Timophon">Τιμοφῶν</name>
                    </persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Lysistrate. Kleippe. Timophon.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Three names are inscribed above the heads of the figures, from left to right:
                    Λυσιστράτη, Κλείππη, Τιμοφῶν (in Lysistrate’s name the first two letters are cut
                    slightly higher than the rest). Timophon is most plausibly the father and
                    Kleippe and the infant form a mother-and-child group; Clairmont suggests that
                    Lysistrate died in childbirth and that Kleippe is the firstborn of Timophon and
                    Lysistrate. The lekythos is by the same hand as CAT 3.745, with inscriptions cut
                    by the same letter-cutter; the two monuments belonged to a single family
                    precinct.</p></div>
            

